// iap-strings.xcstrings.patch — proposed merge fragment for
// App/Resources/Localizable.xcstrings (issue #200, Phase 1.a).
//
// MANUAL MERGE INSTRUCTIONS:
//   1. Open App/Resources/Localizable.xcstrings.
//   2. Copy each top-level entry from the `strings` object below into the
//      existing file's `strings` object (alphabetic order is preserved by
//      Xcode on save — no need to sort).
//   3. Do NOT touch `sourceLanguage` / `version`.
//   4. After merge: run `ASCRegister validate --xcstrings <path>` — it will
//      confirm en + zh-Hant coverage for every gc.* and iap.* key.
//
// Locale coverage in this fragment:
//   - en      → filled (source language; product-appropriate marketing copy)
//   - zh-Hant → filled (user-facing review-ready translation)
//   - ja, zh-Hans, es, th, ko → "<TRANSLATE>" — to be filled by the
//     translation-agent flow (foundations.md §L10n).
//
// Total: 2 keys × 7 locales = 14 string units. 2 × 2 = 4 filled,
// 2 × 5 = 10 marked <TRANSLATE>.
//
// File extension `.xcstrings.patch` mirrors gc-strings.xcstrings.patch
// precedent — Xcode will NOT try to parse this as a string catalog. The
// JSON body below (from the opening `{` to the matching closing `}`) is
// valid JSON; the C-style header comments above are stripped.

{
  "strings" : {
    "iap.remove_ads.name" : {
